### Best practices
- **Use `.mdc` extension** â€” All rule files must use `.mdc` extension
- **Keep rules lightweight** â€” They consume tokens in every conversation
- **Be specific, not vague** â€” "Read GOALS.md first" beats "be helpful"
- **Use examples** â€” Show desired output format
- **Include update instructions** â€” Define when/how to modify files
- **Test and iterate** â€” Refine based on actual usage

### Tradeoffs to consider
- Memory (always present) vs. RAG (retrieved on-demand)
- Specificity vs. flexibility
- Rule length vs. context window cost

